ğŸ”¥ Tech Scenario (Why Companies Use Two Pointers)

Two pointers are used when:

Data is sorted

Or we need pair comparison

Or we need in-place operation

Or we need min/max from ends

This saves:

Time (O(n) instead of O(nÂ²))

Memory (no extra arrays)

| Question                             | If YES                   |
| ------------------------------------ | ------------------------ |
| Do I have two ends (start + end)?    | Use two pointers         |
| Do pointers move based on condition? | Use `while`              |
| Do I stop when they meet/cross?      | Use `while left < right` |
| Is movement not fixed?               | NEVER use `for`          |


| What you want   | Syntax                    |
| --------------- | ------------------------- |
| Get element     | `arr[index]`              |
| Loop until meet | `while left < right`      |
| Compare         | `arr[left] == arr[right]` |
| Move pointers   | `left += 1`, `right -= 1` |
